<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-570] Empty surefire reports when a multi-module project is ran with multiple report directories in surefire-report configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-570</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With a multi-module project, if the reporting configuration set multiple report directories (in the parent POM), then the report / report-only goals generate empty report.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main / aggregated report says this is 0 Tests.&lt;br/&gt;
Module reports are empty html files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached project is a sample project to reproduce this ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The parent POM reporting conf explicitely set 2 reporting directories.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the &quot;parent&quot; POM :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mvn surefire-report:report ==&amp;gt; normal report per modules, nothing to say&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mvn clean&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mvn surefire-report:report -Daggregate=true  ==&amp;gt; parent report with 0 tests, empty html report for modules&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;mvn surefire-report:report; mvn surefire-report:report-only -Daggregate=true ==&amp;gt; idem, parent report with 0 tests, empty html report for modules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Tested on Windows XP &amp;amp; Linux (Ubuntu 09.04) with Maven 2.0.10</environment>
